The '''2005 [[Monte Carlo Masters]]''' was a men's [[tennis]] tournament played on [[Clay court|outdoor clay courts]]. It was the 99th edition of the event and was part of the [[ATP Masters Series]] of the [[2005 ATP Tour]]. It took place from 11 April through 17 April 2005.<ref name="info"/>

The men's singles was headlined by [[List of ATP number 1 ranked players|World No. 1]] [[Roger Federer]], [[Marat Safin]] and [[Tim Henman]]. Other top seeds were [[Gastón Gaudio]], [[Carlos Moyà]], [[Guillermo Coria]], [[Joachim Johansson]] and [[Ivan Ljubičić]].

==Champions==
===Singles===
{{main|2005 Monte Carlo Masters – Singles}}
{{flagicon|ESP}} '''[[Rafael Nadal]]''' defeated {{flagicon|ARG}} [[Guillermo Coria]], 6–3, 6–1, 0–6, 7–5

===Doubles===
{{main|2005 Monte Carlo Masters – Doubles}}
{{flagicon|IND}} '''[[Leander Paes]]''' / {{flagicon|SCG}} '''[[Nenad Zimonjić]]''' defeated {{flagicon|USA}} [[Bob Bryan]] / {{flagicon|USA}} [[Mike Bryan]], walkover

