{{TennisEventInfo|2013|Monte-Carlo Rolex Masters| | date=13 – 21 April | edition=107th | draw=56S / 24D | surface=[[Clay court|Clay]] | prize_money=€2,998,495 | location=[[Monte Carlo]], [[Monaco]] | champs={{flagicon|SRB}} [[Novak Djokovic]] <ref name="ms">{{cite web|title=2013 Monte Carlo Men's Singles draw|url=http://www.atpworldtour.com/en/scores/archive/monte-carlo/410/2013/draws?matchType=singles|website=www.atpworldtour.com|publisher=[[Association of Tennis Professionals]] (ATP)}}</ref> | champd={{flagicon|FRA}} [[Julien Benneteau]] / {{flagicon|SRB}} [[Nenad Zimonjić]] }}
The '''2013 [[Monte-Carlo Rolex Masters]]''' was a men's [[tennis]] tournament for male professional players, played from 13 April through 22 April 2013, on [[Clay court|outdoor clay courts]]. It was the 107th edition of the annual [[Monte Carlo Masters]] tournament, which was sponsored by [[Rolex]] for the fifth time. It took place at the [[Monte Carlo Country Club]] in [[Roquebrune-Cap-Martin]], France, near [[Monte Carlo]], [[Monaco]].
[[Rafael Nadal]] was the eight-time defending champion, but suffered his first defeat at the tournament since his debut in [[2003 Monte Carlo Masters|2003]] (he missed the tournament in 2004 due to injury), by losing in the final to [[Novak Djokovic]]. The defeat ended a [[Rafael Nadal's 46-match winning streak at the Monte-Carlo Masters|46-match winning streak]] dating back to the first of his eight consecutive titles at the tournament, in 2005.<ref>[http://www.abc.net.au/news/2013-04-22/djokovic-dethrones-nadal-in-monte-carlo/4642428?section=sport Djokovic dethrones Nadal in Monte Carlo - ABC Grandstand Sport - ABC News (Australian Broadcasting Corporation)]</ref>
==Points and prize money== ===Points distribution=== Because the Monte Carlo Masters is the non-mandatory [[Masters 1000]] event, special rules regarding points distribution are in place. The Monte Carlo Masters counts as one of a player's 500 level tournaments, while distributing Masters 1000 points.<ref>[http://www.atpworldtour.com/Rankings/Rankings-FAQ.aspx#requirements Ranking points]</ref>
