{{Unreferenced|date=December 2006}} {{Infobox WorldScouting | type = organization | image =Association des Guides du Cameroun.png | caption = Guide Association of Cameroon | name = Association des Guides du Cameroun | headquarters = | location = | country = Cameroon | f-date = 1943 | founder = | award-for = | members = 3,000 | chiefscouttitle = | chiefscout = | owner = | affiliation = [[World Association of Girl Guides and Girl Scouts]] }} The '''Association des Guides du Cameroun''' (AGC, ''Guide Association of Cameroon'') is the national [[Girl Guides|Guiding]] organization of [[Cameroon]]. It serves 3,000 members (as of 2003). Founded in 1943, the girls-only organization became an associate member of the [[World Association of Girl Guides and Girl Scouts]] in 1972 and a full member in 2014.
