'''Sir Herbert Miles Road''' is an eastern coastal road in the [[British Overseas Territories|British Overseas Territory]] of [[Gibraltar]]. It was a new road in 1917 replacing a track that previously gave access to [[Catalan Bay]]. The [[Caleta Hotel]] and [[La Mamela Restaurant]] lie along this road.<ref>{{cite book|title=Lonely Planet Spain|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=WttmSt7kPmMC&pg=PA742|accessdate=2 May 2013|year=2007|publisher=Lonely Planet|isbn=978-1-74104-554-3|page=742}}</ref> At the Caleta Hotel, Sir Herbert Miles Road overlooks Catalan Bay.<ref name="AverbuckBedford2009">{{cite book|last1=Averbuck|first1=Alexis|last2=Bedford|first2=Neal|title=Lonely Planet|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=0jpUlPrDRFoC&pg=PA1039|accessdate=2 May 2013|year=2009|publisher=Lonely Planet|isbn=978-1-74104-917-6|page=1039}}</ref>

